    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1914-09-28T04:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1914-09-28T04:00:00-05:00" n="330"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d330">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 763.72111/899</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé d’Affaires in China</hi> (<persName
                        corresp="#p_MJVA1" type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">MacMurray</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <dateline>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>, <lb/>
                    <placeName>
                        <hi rend="italic">Peking</hi>
                    </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-09-28T17:00:00+08:00">
                        <hi rend="italic">September 28, 1914, 5 p.m.</hi>
                    </date>
                    <lb/> [<hi rend="italic">Received September 29, 10:30 a.m.</hi>] </dateline>
                <p rend="center">[Telegram]</p>
                <p>The Foreign Office informs me that it has had occasion to protest to the Japanese
                    Government against the fact that, in disregard of the zone delimited by
                    agreement with China, Japanese forces have occupied Weihsien.</p>
                <p>The Chinese Government now learns further that Japanese forces are proceeding
                    westward from that point and have taken possession of several mines.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_MJVA1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">MacMurray</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
